Description: Two joining sherds of wall of East Greek pottery cup; interior glazed; exterior: two glaze bands below reserved area; incised inscription on exterior; another sherd was once glued to it, but has been broken off and has no inventory number.
Curator's comments: Perhaps the transcription of the text should not have a capital letter, even if we would espect a dedicatory formula. No personal name exists with this sequence of letters. However, even as a common noun or adjective there is very little at all similar that is attested.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.387)
